sentences: He was injured in 1996 and began to then focus on music.
Eventually arriving in New York City, he recorded his album I Am with producers Pop Rox in late 2003.

It was released on Octone Records in 2004, and he toured as opening act for such artists as Maroon 5, Dave Matthews Band, Blues Traveler, Gavin Degraw, G Love & Special Sauce, The Funky Meters, Pat McGee Band, Everclear, The Clarks, Hanson, and Sister Hazel.
Tolcher's song "Sooner or Later" was the theme song for ABC's 2004–2005 series Life As We Know It.
His song "Mission Responsible" was used as part of a public service announcement for the American Lung Association in 2004.
His EP In the Meantime was released on March 10, 2009, and features "Speed Feels Better", "Wanting You Now", "Speed Feels Better Acoustic", and "Speed Feels Better" video.
Tolcher released his second full length album "Eleven" on May 4, 2015.
In 2016 Michael had the good fortune of meeting REO Speedwagon at the Chicago White Sox game while singing the national anthem.
